Randomized parameters: 

dictionary: 
    dps - degrees per second
    mdps -  milidegrees per second
    LSB - Least Significant Bit
    U - Continuous Uniform Distribution (Constant)
    N - Continuous Normal Distribution (Gauss)
    g - gravitational constant 
    g - mili (tousandth of) gravitational constant 


input:


output:
- angular velocity: 
    (based on 3 sigma criterium, scaled down for lower measurement ranges)
    ~ (  0 ,  245) [dps] -> U(-0.004375, 0.004375) + N(0,   1.49) [dps]
    ~ (245 ,  500) [dps] -> U(-0.008750, 0.008750) + N(0,   6.25) [dps]
    ~ (500 , 2000) [dps] -> U(-0.035000, 0.035000) + N(0, 100.00) [dps]

- linear acceleration sensivity:
    (based on 3 sigma criterium, scaled down for lower measurement ranges)
    ~ (0 ,  2) [g] -> U(-0.0305, 0.0305) + N(0,   56.25) [mg]
    ~ (2 ,  4) [g] -> U(-0.0610, 0.0610) + N(0,  225.00) [mg]
    ~ (4 ,  8) [g] -> U(-0.1220, 0.1220) + N(0,  900.00) [mg]
    ~ (8 , 16) [g] -> U(-0.2440, 0.2440) + N(0, 3600.00) [mg]